2. Check whether `l` has reached the end of the list before `r` has reached the end of the list. If so, the kth smallest element is those elements that have been seen by `l` so far.
3. If `l` has not reached the end of the list before `r` has reached the end of the list, move `l` and `r` towards the end of the list until they meet. At this point, the elements that have been included in the kth smallest element are those that have been seen by `r` so far, and the elements that have been included in the (k-1)th smallest element are those that have been seen by `l` so far.
4. If `l` and `r` meet at the beginning of the list, the (k-1)th smallest element is the whole list.

